I am deeply saddened to hear the news about the passing of Jerry Richardson. Coming out of college I had a foot surgery that brought many questions to my stock as a player, and Mr. Richardson still bet on me. He bet on me when my career was in question due to more injuries that kept me sidelined. 

Because of his confidence in me I played football as a panther for 10 years, which is part of the confidence I have now to continue to bet on myself! 

Thank you!

Rest in peace Mr. Richardson 
(My condolences to the Richardson family)

We are SO excited to show you what we’ve been up to “Lately”! Join us Saturday, November 25th on @wccbcharlotte for the premiere of Lately with @nataliestewar1 and @jonathanstewar1! 📺 #lately #premiere #broadcast

New season, same us. 💛🧡❤️ 

It’s been a busy year working on our new show, LATELY, with Natalie & Jonathan Stewart, with @bahakelentertainment. We are so grateful for this opportunity to develop a series where we get to share our love of two things we’re passionate about, food and people. 

Charlotte Lately’s mission is to celebrate the authenticity, creativity, and people of Charlotte. We did this with our social media platform and print publication but this show has given us the opportunity to really be able to share these stories in an impactful way. 

It has truly been an honor for us to learn about the people behind these different businesses. We walked away from this season so inspired by the good things happening in our community and can’t wait to share it with you guys. 

-Natalie & Jonathan Stewart
